07Z","body":"I have three hard drive (C, D and E), and I have some tests, Here is the results.\r\n\r\n- when zap.bat located at drive C, %HOMEPATH% can find .ZAP_JVM.properties\r\n- when zap.bat located at another drive except drive C like drive D, %HOMEPATH% can't find .ZAP_JVM.properties\r\n\r\n```\r\nC:\\Users\\scofield>if exist \"%HOMEPATH%\\OWASP ZAP\\.ZAP_JVM.properties\" (echo true) else (echo false)\r\ntrue\r\n\r\nC:\\Users\\scofield>D:\r\n\r\nD:\\>if exist \"%HOMEPATH%\\OWASP ZAP\\.ZAP_JVM.properties\" (echo true) else (echo false)\r\nfalse\r\n\r\nD:\\>E:\r\n\r\nE:\\>if exist \"%HOMEPATH%\\OWASP ZAP\\.ZAP_JVM.properties\" (echo true) else (echo f\r\nalse)\r\nfalse\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think maybe windows can automatically add current drive when use %HOMEPATH%. So when we use start zap in drive C, everything is fine. When we start in another drive, %HOMEPATH% is not we want.","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/zaproxy/zaproxy/issues/comments/280971991/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"ScofieldXu","id":6541476,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY1NDE0NzY=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6541476?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ScofieldXu","html_url":"https://github.com/ScofieldXu","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ScofieldXu/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ScofieldXu/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ScofieldXu/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ScofieldXu/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ScofieldXu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ScofieldXu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ScofieldXu/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ScofieldXu/events{/privacy}","receiv